         <span style="color: #003366;">
          News &amp; Events Highlights
         </span>
        </h1>
        <div href="/news/index">
         <hr/>
         <h3>
          <a href="https://sites.google.com/ucsd.edu/ethnicstudiesnewsletter/home?authuser=0">
           <span style="color: #016691;">
            Ethnic Studies Newsletter
           </span>
          </a>
         </h3>
        </div>
        <div href="/news/index">
         <hr/>
         <h3 class="zfr3Q OmQG5e">
          <span style="color: black;">
           Ethnic Studies Community Building Event
          </span>
         </h3>
         <p style="text-align: justify;">
          <span style="color: black;">
           Undergraduates, graduate students and faculty, thank for making the Ethnic Studies Mixer on December 5th, 2018 a great success. Our community is stronger and united because of your
          </span>
          participation and efforts. Students are currently mobilizing and starting a new Ethnic Studies Club at UCSD.
          <span style="color: black;">
          </span>
         </p>
         <hr/>
         <h3>
          <span style="color: black;">
           Triton Day and Transfer Triton Day
           <br/>
          </span>
         </h3>
         <p style="text-align: justify;">
          <span style="color: black;">
           The Department of Ethnic Studies will be participating in Triton Day on Saturday, April 13th and Transfer Triton Day on Saturday, May 11th, 2019. Visit us at the Town Square during our tabling to learn more about our Ethnic Studies major, minor and courses.
           <br/>
          </span>
         </p>
         <hr/>
         <h3>
          <span style="color: black;">
           Nicholas Papadopoulos Endowed Lecture in Gay &amp; Lesbian Studies
          </span>
          <a href="_images/PapFlyerPurple.jpg">
           <img alt="PapFlyerPurple.jpg" class="right" height="204" src="_images/PapFlyerPurple.jpg" width="130"/>
          </a>
         </h3>
         <p style="text-align: justify;">
          <span style="color: #000000;">
           CGS, BSP, and the Global Forum present the 2019 Nicholas Papadopoulos Endowed Lecture in Gay &amp; Lesbian Studies. "Until All Of Us Are Free: LGBTQ+ Activism in the Time of Trump" featuring Andrea Ritchie - attorney, organizer and author. Click here for the event flyer -&gt;
          </span>
         </p>
         <hr/>
         <h3>
          <span style="color: black;">
           Ethnic Studies Colloquium
          </span>
          <a href="news-and-events/monika.png">
           <img alt="monika.png" class="right" height="164" src="news-and-events/monika.png" width="130"/>
          </a>
         </h3>
         <p style="text-align: justify;">
          <span style="color: #000000;">
           Join us Friday, March 8th from 2:00 pm-3:30 pm in Social Sciences Building Room 107 for a talk by Alumna Monika Gosin. Click here for the event flyer -&gt;
          </span>
         </p>
